More than two thirds of French
voters expect President  Nicolas Sarkozy  to lose the 2012
election, and a majority feel Foreign Minister  Alain Juppe  would
make a better candidate for the ruling UMP party, a poll found.  The survey by Viavoice showed 26 percent of voters said
theyâ€™d rather see Juppe represent the UMP, compared with 21
percent who prefer Sarkozy. Liberation newspaper commissioned
